The paper proposes a tool that automatically infers points-to specifications for analyzing programs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The tool uses unit tests to observe the behavior of library code, which involves program synthesis (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also evaluates the tool's performance on a benchmark of Android apps, which involves security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). Finally, the paper emphasizes the tool's ability to improve precision, which is a common goal in machine learning (cs.LG).
